<item>
            <title>[LU-9888] conf-sanity test_32b: test 32b failed with 1</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9888</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&#160; This issue was created by maloo for Bob Glossman &amp;lt;bob.glossman@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/7907a6a4-8386-11e7-b90b-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/7907a6a4-8386-11e7-b90b-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_32b failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;test_32b failed with 1
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While this fail is in the same test as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9826&quot; title=&quot;conf-sanity: test 32b failed with 1&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9826&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9826&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; it is seen after landing the fix for that fail.&lt;br/&gt;
Doesn&apos;t look like the fail is due to out of space anymore, so creating a fresh Jira ticket.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: conf-sanity 32b&lt;/p&gt;</description>
