                            <comment id="207055" author="utopiabound" created="Thu, 31 Aug 2017 14:39:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/28464/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/28464/&lt;/a&gt; landed with a larger disk2_7-zfs image and re-enabled this test (it passed with ZFS 0.6.5.9).&#160; Quota verification isn&apos;t enabled for ZFS prior to 0.7.0, and this test fails for 0.7.0.&#160; This test may NEVER have successfully passed quota verification.&#160; I think the 40K value may be correct and we can fix the image by adding a&#160;&lt;tt&gt;blimit&lt;/tt&gt; file with &lt;tt&gt;40960&lt;/tt&gt; as a value.&#160; New images use 40K and have blimit, old images defaulted to 20K (which gets used if no blimit file is present).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
